Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers State is considering another lockdown as the state witnesses a surge in the number of COVID-19 cases. The total number of infec­tions in the state is 3,398 as of December 28, the sixth-high­est in Nigeria. The number of deaths from COVID-19 in the state is 64. The total number of con­firmed cases in the state as of May 24 was 116. Seven months after, the state has recorded over 3,000 new cases. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “I have allowed the church to be worshipping with this number because I am a Christian, but I can tell you before the end of the year so many stringent measures will be taken, we are going to shut down,” Wike said at a church service in Ikwerre Local Government Area of the state. The governor added: “Peo­ple in churches, markets, and other public places were no longer adhering to COVID-19 requirements and protocols because most of them think it is not real. Crossover Night: CAN Asks Churches To Close Services By 11p.m Customers Resort To PoS Amid Disappointing Bank ATMs “It’s not real because it has not happened to you; nobody has died whom you know. “When somebody has died and the person was close to you, you will know that COVID-19 is real. “If you don’t comply, I have no choice but to shut down churches – Pentecos­tal, Catholic, Anglican. “I have no choice be­cause when you have it, who spends the money? It is the state that treats.” SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION